        "id": "OCF-I",
        "label": "Royal Texts in the Sacramentary of Gellone",
        "labelFr": "Textes royaux du Sacramentaire de Gellone",
        "openatlasClass": "E33 Linguistic Object",
        "systemClass": "artifact",
        "viewClass": "artifact",
        "type": "ordo_text",
        "tradition": "OCF",
        "date": "790–00",
        "description": "The earliest surviving liturgical formulas associated with coronation ceremonial, found in the late 8th-century Sacramentary of Gellone. Contains four royal benedictions copied from older sources. None remained permanently in the French ceremony, but three reappear in later texts. The fourth (Christe Deus oriens) is unique to this sacramentary."
      }
